# Component & Screen Rules

## Styling
- Use NativeWind classes only. Never `StyleSheet.create()` for colors, spacing, or layout.
- All colors via theme CSS variables: `bg-primary`, `text-secondary`, `border-border`. See @DESIGN_SYSTEM.md for full token list.
- Spacing uses Tailwind scale mapped to 4px base: `p-4` = 16px, `gap-3` = 12px.
- Border radius: `rounded-md` (12px) for cards/buttons, `rounded-sm` (6px) for chips, `rounded-full` for avatars.
- Shadow: one level only — `shadow-card`. Use surface color differences for depth hierarchy.

## Component Structure
```
// 1. Imports
// 2. Interface (props)
// 3. Component function
// 4. Sub-components (if small and only used here)
// 5. Export
```

## Component Rules
- Props interface always defined. No inline object types.
- Destructure props in function signature.
- Loading state: always use Skeleton component, never a spinner in place of content.
- Empty state: always render EmptyState component with illustration + message + CTA.
- Error state: always handle. Show user-friendly message via Toast, never blank screen.
- Every interactive element: `accessibilityLabel` + `accessibilityRole`. Min tap target 44×44px.
- Animations via `react-native-reanimated` only. Respect `useReducedMotion()`.
- Haptics via `expo-haptics` for: check-in success, follow toggle, submission success. Nothing else.

## Screen (Expo Router) Rules
- Screens in `app/` use default export.
- Wrap content in `ScreenContainer` (handles SafeArea + scroll + keyboard avoidance).
- Data fetching in a custom hook, not in the screen component body.
- Screen loads: show skeleton → fetch → render data OR show error.
- Pull-to-refresh on any list screen.

## Gluestack UI Usage
- Use Gluestack primitives for: Button, Input, Select, Switch, Toast, Modal, Actionsheet, Badge, Avatar, Spinner, Divider.
- Extend with custom components for Masjidy-specific UI (MosqueCard, TrustBadge, PrayerTimeRow, etc).
- Override Gluestack styles through theme config, not per-instance style props.

## RTL
- Never use `left`/`right` for layout — use `start`/`end` (NativeWind: `ps-4` not `pl-4`).
- Test Arabic layout after every new screen.
- Numbers in prayer times stay LTR even in RTL layouts.

## Images
- Mosque photos: lazy load on profile screen. Never in list cards or bootstrap payload.
- Empty photo: use SVG placeholder (mosque silhouette), never a broken image icon.
- All custom SVGs in `assets/icons/` at 24px grid to match Phosphor style.
